    "summary": "After receiving first-year certificates for both computer science and applied mathematics, Wouter has received a Master of Science in applied mathematics and has successfully finished a PhD in applied mathematics with applications in psychology, sociology and behavioral economics at the Eindhoven University of Technology. Subsequently, Wouter has worked as a scientific software engineer and designer and project leader at ASML. \n\nThe three subsequent years, Wouter has worked as a business unit manager for Nspyre mainly in the high-tech industry. In this function, he was responsible for significant increase in turnover and profit over three years. Moreover, he was responsible for several key customer accounts. In addition, he was responsible for an enormous boost in recruitment in a niche market. \n\nFor 4 years, Wouter has worked as Research and Development Manager and member of the management team at ABS Laundry Business Solutions. After fulfilling the role of Release Train Engineer for 1.5 and Chief Product Owner for 2 years, he is now working as Solution Owner at ASML. He speaks multiple languages and received exceptionally high scores on the Reasoning for Business Managerial & Graduate competency tests (97th percentile and up).\n\n\u2022\tHis ambition in life is to challenge himself and reach seemingly unreachable targets with his customers. As a result he achieves maximum business value;\n\u2022\tWouter is often described by others as proactive, having a clear goal, focusses on priorities, thinks in terms of win/win, listens well, and finds synergy. He does all this with an enormous amount of energy and will to succeed;\n\u2022\tHe considers project management, account management, people management, consulting and setting up new enterprises as his main competences;\n\u2022\tHis specialties can be found in the areas of convincement, trust, and drive to succeed.",
